(41, 10, 41, 50, 2, 3, 3, 'much displeased with James and John', 'Strife and Humility in Leadership', 'This connection highlights the theme of strife among the disciples in Mark 10:41, which contrasts with the call for humility and selflessness in Philippians 2:3. Both passages emphasize the importance of valuing others over oneself to avoid discord.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 41, 41, 9, 33, 36, NULL, 'Dispute Over Greatness', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of disputes among the disciples regarding greatness and status. In Mark 9:33-36, the disciples argue about who should be the greatest, while in Mark 10:41, the ten are displeased with James and John for seeking positions of honor.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
