(41, 10, 43, 41, 9, 35, 35, 'shall be your minister', 'Servanthood in Leadership', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of greatness through servanthood. Mark 10:43 states that to be great, one must be a minister, while Mark 9:35 teaches that to be first, one must be a servant of all.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 43, 42, 9, 48, 48, 'whosoever will be great among you', 'Greatness through Humility', 'Both passages emphasize that true greatness is found in serving others and being humble. Mark highlights that the greatest must be a minister, while Luke states that the least among you shall be great.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 43, 48, 5, 13, 13, 'shall be your minister', 'Service and Greatness in Community', 'This connection highlights the theme of serving others as a path to greatness. Both passages emphasize the importance of ministering and serving one another in love, contrasting worldly views of power with a call to humility and service.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 43, 60, 5, 5, 6, 'great among you, shall be your minister', 'Humility and Service in Leadership', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of humility in leadership. Mark 10:43 highlights that greatness comes through serving others, while 1 Peter 5:5-6 encourages submission and humility among believers.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 45, 40, 20, 28, 28, 'to minister, and to give his life a ransom for many', 'Connection of Service and Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Son of man in serving others and giving his life as a ransom. The identical phrasing reinforces the theme of selfless ministry and sacrifice for many.', 'theme', 0.657, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 45, 50, 2, 5, 8, 'to minister, and to give his life', 'Servanthood and Humility in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of Christ''s servanthood and humility. Both passages emphasize that Jesus came to serve and gave his life, demonstrating obedience and selflessness.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 45, 47, 8, 9, 9, 'to give his life a ransom for many', 'Service and Sacrifice of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of Christ''s selflessness. Mark 10:45 highlights Jesus'' role in giving his life, while 2 Corinthians 8:9 illustrates his choice to become poor for others'' benefit.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 45, 56, 2, 14, 14, 'give his life a ransom for many', 'Redemption and Service Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of redemption through self-giving. Mark highlights Jesus'' purpose to ''give his life a ransom for many,'' while Titus speaks of Him giving Himself ''for us'' to redeem and purify. This connection highlights the sacrificial nature of Jesus'' mission.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 45, 43, 10, 15, 15, 'give his life a ransom for many', 'Connection of Sacrificial Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying down one''s life. Mark highlights giving life as a ransom, while John specifies laying down life for the sheep.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 45, 43, 13, 14, 14, 'to minister', 'Service and Humility in Action', 'This connection highlights the theme of service, as both passages emphasize the importance of ministering to others. Mark 10:45 speaks of the Son of man coming to minister, while John 13:14 illustrates this by showing the act of washing feet as a model for serving one another.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 45, 42, 22, 26, 27, 'to minister, and to give his life', 'Servanthood and Leadership', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of serving others. Mark highlights Jesus'' role as a servant who gives his life, while Luke contrasts greatness with servitude, illustrating that true leadership is found in serving.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 46, 40, 20, 29, 34, 'blind Bartimeus, the son of Timeus', 'Healing of Blind Men', 'Both passages emphasize the healing of blind individuals near Jericho. In Mark, blind Bartimeus is mentioned, while Matthew describes two blind men who seek Jesus'' mercy. This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' compassion and miraculous healing.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 46, 43, 9, 8, 8, NULL, 'Connection of Blindness and Begging', 'This connection highlights the theme of blindness and begging in both passages. In Mark, Bartimeus is described as a blind beggar, while in John, the formerly blind man is recognized by his neighbors as someone who sat and begged.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 46, 42, 16, 22, 22, 'begging', 'Connection of Begging and Death', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of begging and the fate of the beggar. In Mark, Bartimeus is a beggar, while in Luke, the beggar''s death leads to a significant afterlife experience.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 46, 44, 3, 2, 3, NULL, 'Healing of the Beggars', 'Both passages emphasize individuals who are begging for alms due to their disabilities. This connection highlights the theme of seeking help and the miraculous healing that follows in the ministry of Jesus and the apostles.', 'theme', 0.293, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 47, 41, 1, 24, 24, 'Jesus of Nazareth', 'Recognition of Jesus'' Identity', 'This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus as the Son of David in Mark 10:47 and as the Holy One of God in Mark 1:24. Both passages emphasize the acknowledgment of Jesus'' divine authority and identity by different groups.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 47, 40, 9, 27, 27, 'Son of David', 'Blind Men Calling for Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''Son of David'' as the title used by blind individuals seeking mercy from Jesus. This connection highlights a consistent recognition of Jesus'' messianic identity among those in need.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 47, 40, 15, 22, 22, 'thou Son of David', 'Crying for Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize a plea for mercy addressed to Jesus as ''Son of David.'' This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus'' messianic identity by individuals in need.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 47, 66, 22, 16, 16, 'Jesus, thou Son of David', 'Connection of Davidic Lineage', 'This connection highlights the acknowledgment of Jesus as the ''Son of David'' in Mark, linking to His declaration as the ''root and offspring of David'' in Revelation. Both passages emphasize Jesus'' Davidic lineage, underscoring His messianic identity.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 47, 42, 18, 36, 37, 'Jesus of Nazareth', 'Recognition of Jesus'' Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the recognition of Jesus as ''Jesus of Nazareth.'' In Mark, the blind man calls out to Jesus, identifying him as the ''Son of David,'' while in Luke, the crowd informs the blind man that ''Jesus of Nazareth'' is passing by.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
